{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2ca39573-ed47-456e-b84e-a11bd2e6c966","content":"To switch to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC), you need to make these changes:\n\n**1. Configure your NuGet.org package** — In NuGet.org account settings, register a trusted publisher linking your GitHub repo/workflow to the package.\n\n**2. Update your workflow:**\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write  # Required for OIDC token\n\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      # Build/pack steps...\n\n      - name: Push to NuGet\n        run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg\n          --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n**Key differences:**\n- Add `permissions: id-token: write` to the job\n- Remove the `--api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}` argument\n- No secret needed — the OIDC token is exchanged automatically\n- You can delete the `NUGET_API_KEY` repository secret once confirmed working\n\n**3. On NuGet.org** — Go to your package → Manage → Publishing → Add Trusted Publisher. Provide your GitHub org/repo, workflow filename, and optionally an environment name.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"acd9c02d-80c3-4be8-bc4a-e2015350f94d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about switching from using a NuGet API key secret to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC) in their GitHub Actions publish workflow. This is a general knowledge question about GitHub Actions and NuGet trusted publishing - I don't need to look at any specific files since there's no repository here.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about what changes are needed to switch to NuGet trusted publishing with OIDC.","outputTokens":407,"requestId":"1413:214B1C:1B4A0B1:1E5C291:69FA9057"},"id":"0705c826-fc5a-4061-a572-945308b5ed87","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:50:41.101Z","parentId":"29aea261-10a1-42e2-bdd3-05fa3fa0be9f"}
